What you need to know:

"Nobody is training even the Brazilian who joined the team recently. Players are always accused of boycotts before big matches, but fans should also understand our morale is down because we are broke, in debt and have no food," said a senior player, who did not wish to be named."I hear they always bash journalists for reporting on the boycott and want them to reveal our names. But it is the truth they are reporting and we are just fighting for our right," said another player.